caption: Very rude staff, I was not aware I was not able to bring my small pup in for a pick up order from the counter ( for a whole 5 seconds) and Instead of politely informing me the pup was not allowed I was berated by a very rude staff member and my food was tossed to me in a rude manner. Then the Manager continued to support the rude staff member. I  will not be returning as the staff is very rude and will likely never order from Pot Belly again.

I love potbelly’s subs.  There are No other Sub places that are better in my opinion.  Their sandwiches are not huge but the quality is fantastic and the regular sub is enough to fill me up.

There isnt much variety here but their subs are as good as can be expected. They do have good customer service generally, theres always a couple of workers in any franchise that have little drive in their work ethic.
Food is normal for Potbelly's (good), but the abundant seating at this location is what really earns the fifth star.
Great food, friendly service.
Awesome service! Good food, great atmosphere and great staff.

Quick service despite the long line, great listening skills by the lady taking my condiment requests (didn't have to repeat myself despite the noise), and as always, Potbelly sandwiches are amazing. If you know you'll be in a hurry, I suggest ordering via the mobile app and picking up, it'll be more convenient for you, but just as delicious!

Busy, slow, and the manager is constantly yelling at his employees about some things or another. Your sandwich won't taste as good when the young lady making it is holding back tears. I've been to Potbelly's all over Chicago and this is definitely the worst. There are other Potbelly locations nearby that are much more pleasant, would definitely skip this!
Its an amazing place. Great sandwich and delicious smoothies. Loved it.
Mediocre they  never have your food ready when you order online

It's Potbelly, so you know what you're getting. The lunch rush is manageable here and they have plenty of seating. A good place to sit and eat by yourself, or with one or two others, and maybe even get a little work done. Friendly staff and as efficient as any other Potbelly location without the same crushing crowds at lunchtime.
Tuna Sandwich....yummmm
Great place to eat lunch. Food was amazing.

Basically it's exactly what you expect from a chain sandwich shop.  Better than subway, worse than local places.  I just wish their salads were a bit better, I think the spinach and bacon isn't as fresh as it could be.
My favorite lunch spot. It's hard to miss the lines during the rush hour, but they are always quick with making the sandwiches and that staff is friendly and awesome.

I believe I ordered the pizza sub with everything on it. Anyways, beware of the jalapeños. They are spicier than you think. Besides that point, there is only one bathroom per gender, has two floors of space to sit and the second floor is earn giving feeling of a cabin or lounge texture.

Possibly one of my favorite places for lunch. Leaps and bounds better than your average Subway for not too much more money, and this one in particular has the River North lunch rush down to a science.
Speed of service during lunch rush is top notch!
Amazing salads and sandwiches.

One of the few fast sub sandwiches places where I never doubt the quality of meat. There aren't a zillion toppings options like Subway, but what the do have has flavor. Mac and cheese is also good if you aren't in the mood for a sandwich, salad, or soup. Really good cookies. Also good for catering if you are getting sandwiches for a group.

Love the Wreck salad with salami, roast beef, turkey, hard boiled egg, swiss cheese, onion, tomato - so good and with great croutons! They have great milkshakes and the best oatmeal chocolate chip cookies! They have a huge menu, reasonable prices and you can't go wrong!
Chili cheeseburger - one of my favorites

+ best sandwich chain in the US, + addicting überdelicious sandwiches, + inexpensive  After traveling a lot through the country I have to say that Potbelly is for sure the best sandwich chain in the US! I love the way they toast the sandwiches including all meat and cheese and top it later with veggies and dressing or mayo.  Besides, you also get soups, salads, shakes and cookies at Potbelly, which are also very tasteful.
